name: England Football
summary: England's humiliating 2-1 defeat to Greece in the Nations League has raised questions about the future of interim manager Lee Carsley. After going behind to a first-half penalty, England pushed for an equalizer and were awarded one in stoppage time, only for Anastasios Pavlidis to score a stunning winner for Greece in the final seconds. The result leaves Carsley with a difficult decision to make about his future with the England U21s, as he had previously stated his intention to return to that role after this match. The match was notable for Greece's tribute to George Baldock, who made history by becoming the first amputee to play in a senior international.

name: Addison's disease
summary: TikTok star Taylor Rousseau Grigg, who tragically passed away at the age of 25, succumbed to Addison's disease, a rare but serious condition that affects the body's ability to produce hormones. Addison's disease occurs when the adrenal glands, located above the kidneys, do not function properly, leading to a deficiency in the hormones cortisol and aldosterone. This deficiency can cause a range of symptoms, including fatigue, weight loss, nausea, and muscle weakness. It is an uncommon condition, but it can be life-threatening if left untreated. Grigg's family has confirmed that Addison's disease, in combination with asthma, was the cause of her untimely death.
